reviews.text: Could use some updating but it was nice and clean! Plenty of supplies in the facilities and well maintained.  The color scheme made me feel as though I had skipped back to my parents generation.... several decades ago.  It's very beige and brown.  However, it is clean and well taken care of. So the color thing could just be me 🙂.  The grounds were very nice.  They had several events occurring at the same time but they did not interfere. Plenty of room for all !

Country thunder was alot of fun. The staff at the  park very pleasant however none where on the same page..  We paid for Premier tickets that took care of the camping and admission.   They charged us money to have the camper filled with water and pumped out when that was already covered in our Premier admission. Over a $150 more and still have not  refunded it.  They did not allow us to use the gates that entered back to the camp ground's . Hopefully next time around the people running country thunder will have it down just a little better .
Saw some boxing. All was Spanish and I couldn't understand it but damn good time!! Definitely a do again!

Went here for a circus that was in town with my wife and kids. Me, my wife and my kids loved it there. The clown act was hilarious. They had a cannon and it was great. There was a batmobile there, jugglers, acrobatics, a stunt man, and popcorn.  The whole time I was in tears because I was laughing so hard.  There's always a reason to stop by to see what's the next event being hosted at there arenas.  Lots of great people and great memories kept there.
Fields were nice. Rest rooms were totally disgusting. For $10 admission  I would expect decent facilities.  Food charges were ridiculous.

The Osceola County Historical Society Experience is amazing and definitely a must see with the family! This place is loaded with Osceolas History and the Staff is Very Knowledgeable! Did I mention it was free 👊😎👊 Have a wonderful Time
An unexpected delight. A wonderful history of Florida and the native Americans here
Love this place. The history it tells is very important for everyone to know.
Wonderful full of Historical fact about Kissimmee and Osceola county
Wonderful place to learn about local and Florida history -- caters to adults and kids alike.

Fun place to hangout and catch a show! The bartenders are attentive and friendly, and they have some great drink specials. Don't be fooled by the small-ish size of the venue... this place is really great for live music. The stage tech here takes his job seriously, and you can tell. Their sound system is on point and the mix is always perfect. I'll be back!

Capone's is the best bar/venue in all of Johnson city. The drinks are made perfect, security is top notch, and the sound man really makes the music the best to its ability. I've played on that stage before. As a musician I can vouch for good sound quality.

They have the nicest, most professional bartenders in the area. Abigail is often there during peak times and she has a contagious smile and positive energy. No matter how busy they are I always receive my drinks and tabs in a timely manner. I have no idea how they do it! I absolutely love the live music and sometimes I find it necessary to escape to the vault and dance just to remind me of how old I am the next day. It’s also a very safe place. I recommend this place for bachelorette parties and late night celebrations.

We came in from out of town for The Steel Woods show. We were in line well before doors were set to open. Despite this, we could not get into the room for the show or get through the bar line more than once. I actually work at a small independent music venue, and the only reason you are even getting 2 stars is the professionalism of your staff. The door guys were fantasic, efficient, and friendly. Your bar was understaffed, but those working were doing the very best they could to keep up with the volume. We basically had to leave before the show was over because we couldn't see anything, were being constantly pushed and it was a miserable experience on the stage side. I'm sure your capacity covers both rooms, but you definitely sold more tickets than the stage side could adequately accommodate. I don't mind a shoulder to shoulder room, but this was beyond the pale and bordering upon unethical. A real disservice to fans.

I always forget about this place when I shouldn't.  Usually a good fun band playing on the weekend which can vary on the genre but that can be a good thing !   No smoking allowed and usually a 5$ cover with a full bar.  There is a lower level that is a separate bar with a dance floor.  Probably best place for that here in Johnson City for now.  Vaping also allowed.   Foosball table in the back.  Staff is usually very helpful with drinks.

Our waitress was so sweet first off, genuinely. Tuesday is kids eat free so already it was a nice perk. My husband and I had the gator tail dinner and it was really great. So atmosphere and food are definitely worth it, also they had a lady in the corner that painted the kids faces and did balloons so my kid approves too. :p

A cool sports bar with plenty of TVs, some arcade games, at a good selection of classic American Bar fare. The wings are really good with a large array of sauces to try. A good beer selection, but only a few beers on tap, and not much available from local breweries. Otherwise, the restaurant is clean and the decor fits in with what you would expect to find at a sports bar.

First time at Gators. The service was nice and attentive, the waitress was polite but the food is really disappointing. It seems microwaved food. In one plate the fries were fresh but in my plate they were cold and staid. The fish was horrible and drenched in oil. Not worth it.

First and last time stepping into this place. I don’t normally write bad reviews since it’s such a dramatic move, but here I am. 
We were immediately seated down. After seating, we didn’t get taken care of. This went on for twenty minutes. Granted a guy asked if we were taken care of, but he never got back to us.
Got disappointed, stood up, and left the store. 

PS
It wasn’t that busy.

The food was delicious and the atmosphere was fun. After asking if they discounted for active duty military members, the manager came over and shared his gratitude for our service with us. We loved the personal touch!

Lots of food, fun, and excitement! Our waitress was wonderful and very friendly. Our 1 year old sat still and was entertained the entire time. Our other children ages 6 and 8 loved the show as well. I've been going to Medieval times for over 30 years and it seems like the red and yellow knight has always won. Our seats were great and right in the center of the arena (we didn't pay extra for VIP) but get there early as the seating is first come first serve. We were extremely stuffed from the delicious food (I can't believe they give each person, including kids, half of a chicken)! We ended up bringing food home with us.

Really fun and exciting place, food is great, service is great, and the entertainment is awesome. If you've never been to a show like it definitely check it out. Even if you've gone it's a fun time regardless.

Only real issue is I feel that initially getting in could be a bit more organized, other than that great experience!

Dinner and a show. Kids loved it. We bought the royalty pass. Dinner was roasted half chicken, tomato soup, buttered toast, corn on cob, and a potato half spiced. Then a small cup of soft serve ice cream. Only detractor was youngest fell getting back into seat. He was fine, caught himself. Make sure to assist the kids back into their seats if they get up for restroom etc. They should include gratuity for the server in the bill.

Place smelled like a barn. And this is where u get to eat. You got used to it but very overwhelming when you get in the arena. Would be great for small kids. My 14 & 15 weren't overly impressed. Way too much food but it was decent. Soup was better with the toast but it came after the fact. Potato was like a wedge from gas station. Not very good.  Row in front had sweet tea. We got lemonade. We couldn't get sweet tea kinda disappointing. All in all not worth the money.

Been going to this since I was a kid, the show is awesome! Its fun to take a step back in time if you love the Medieval era. I have been to NJ, SC, and FL, but the Orlando location is the best one because they have an outside walk through where you can see what it was like in the past from what they wore, ate, built, or see the torture chamber. If you haven't seen the new show this year, I would recommend you come to see the new performance and twists through out the show. No matter what Medieval Times is by far better that the Pirates Voyage and Dixie Stampede, trust me it's worth every penny to see the show!

I enjoyed a delicious seafood feast. For the price you want to come hungry. I only can speak for the raw oysters, crab legs, and lobster. The lobster off the buffet was a bit rubbery. You can ask your server for fresh cooked lobster. That was much better. My server and the rest of the staff I encountered were pleasant. If you like seafood definitely worth a visit. Definitely think salad bar and desert options could be improved.

Worth the price!! Great staff... This is not a place for only tourist. I live in S. Fl where all seafood is readily available, but this is one of my favorite places when I visit Orlando. The managers are excellent as well.

For a buffet I was disappointed.  You spend $50+ and the lobsters you get are so small that you get like 3 or 4 bites. The lobster bisque was really good.  Wasn't happy with the sides.  They didn't look appealing.  The salad section wasn't very good.  We did have a nice waitress and she did try to keep our table clean.  They take pictures then want to charge $20 for it.  It should be included in the price of the meal.  The prime rib was cold and over done

Food was Awesome! Service was Great !  Lobster, Oysters and crab legs were really good. We asked for lobster claws on side with lobster.  a large  selection of other items including stuffed shrimp :) must try!  We had the Mango Margaritas with our meal :)   Was worth the trip and price was good. The staff was so friendly on floor and behind the service area serving. Wait was not to long for a Friday night.  Missed the big lobster on car out front  from last time went  Will be back again.

The hotel we stayed at gave us a 5.00 off coupon and we came down. We looked first buffet did not look fresh so we left and went back to our hotel where they had another kind of lobster feast at the Comfort Inn where they said they accepted all Boston's coupons. They got our business and it was SUPER GREAT. You should keep your buffet full and fresh. You weren't even busy.
